Among the synchronously foldable boards, one of them was damaged by a stuck cable in a length of about 1 meter.
In order to avoid further injury, the board was not continued to be opened.
The astronauts were originally tasked with taking a check-in walk from the Discovery space shuttle and then repairing another solar panel with a defective rotation system. Instead, they had to devote their entire time to repair the damaged solar panel.
