The tool he used, a mini hockey bat, which was insulated against hundreds of volts of tension in solar panels, was five-fold and "whyed" by the station's astronauts.
After completing the operation, Scott Parazynski waited for his companions to open the board completely, and only then packed his tools and returned to the station.
