Parallel to the parliamentary process, which ended today with a congressional vote approving the amendments of the Senate, the government initiated a social dialogue on the regulation on which the law is based, so that both could enter into force before the end of the year.
Representatives from different groups unanimously highlighted the efforts of MEPs and senators in negotiations and agreements, which served to develop the most favorable normative to protect investors, as well as to regulate the activities of companies in order to operate efficiently on the market.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Markets Act, allows the modernisation of financial markets, while at the same time strengthening investor protection, broadens the supervisory rights of the Spanish National Securities Markets Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various inspectors of the European Union.
The new directive allows financial advisory services for specialized companies, but also for natural or legal persons, and in addition to securities distribution companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies, a new financial services company (ESIS), namely financial advisory companies (AFI).
In addition, the law increases the number of systems suitable for carrying out operations involving funds, and thus the addition of multilateral trading platforms and internalisation systems for the execution of orders to be entered into competition with current stock market players.
Furthermore, the Act obliges investment service providers to provide market information regarding the determining aspects of their business profile, their risk-taking and risk management methods, and to keep a record of all operations implemented to facilitate the control of CNMV.
The Economic Committee of Congress has enacted a number of amendments. Of these, it is of paramount importance that securitised debts are treated as "complex" funds due to the high risk to the investor. This was confirmed in connection with the US high-risk mortgage lending (subprime).
On the other hand, the transposition of the directive was also used to legally outline the scope of activities of those with economic and entrepreneurship qualifications. This was done 30 years after the Royal Decree defining the professional functions that could only be performed by economists in 1977.
The Senate proposed the creation of new players in the financial sector, such as the brokerage agent, who works for another account, does not need CNMV permission, and can distribute products or acquire customers to several investment companies at the same time.
