What insurance is right for me?
Motor insurance, which means safety for the owner of the vehicle, brings significant costs to the owner of various damages and depends on several factors, such as age, gender, driving licence, marital status, type and scope of use of the vehicle to be provided.
Buying a car is only the first step.
In fact, choosing the right insurance is often harder than deciding what kind of car you want.
First of all, we need to know what it is about.
The vehicle insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This agreement is embodied in the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company undertakes the compensation for the fixed insurance premium in the event of the occurrence of the damage.
The insurance premium is practically the amount paid for insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, date of obtaining a driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured, its use, and so on.
Insurance companies determine the insurance premium on the basis of the statistics, i.e. a higher amount is paid by those who represent a higher risk of accidents.
That’s why people over the age of 25 or women pay less, because according to statistics, they pose a lower risk because they are more cautious.
Similarly, according to the statements, insurance companies have concluded that married people cause fewer accidents than lonely people.
Frequency is decisive for the type of car.
More frequent use increases the possibility of an accident.
When determining the insurance premium, a number of factors are taken into account by insurance companies.
Therefore, the owner must carefully look into it to choose the most appropriate form of insurance for his profile.
The following will be presented with the most important factors in the selection, so that it is best to adapt to the needs of the insured and to create an acceptable price.
When concluding an insurance contract, people under the age of 25 have to face a number of disadvantages, such as the lack of driving experience and the freshness of driving licences.
Although it is best to be insured against all dangers, there are also more economical solutions.
Careful managers can take out complete insurance with a self-sufficiency, ensuring against all hazards, and the price will also be affordable.
In this type of contract, the insured pays part of the damage.
"The amount of the deductible payable by the insured depends on the insurance premium; the higher the premium, the lower the deductible," says Luis Noguera, head of the Internet insurance intermediary in Spain at First Europa.
Another option is liability insurance extended to third parties, when the customer insures himself against the damage caused to others, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, it will be assured of theft, fire damage and the loss of the car.
- A good word of advice.
If you are not yet 25 years old, be careful and preferably avoid accidents, as this affects the bonus and thus reduce the amounts to be paid in the future.
Bonus is called the discounts provided in relation to the underlying tariff of the insurance company.
The penalty charged compared to the basic tariff is called the málusz.
"The amount of bonus and foliage depends on the insurance company and your profits.
If the company has had a good year, you can afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
Once the age limit of 25 has been exceeded, it is easier for the owners to take out adequate insurance, as the risk of an accident decreases due to the experience gained over the years.
At this time, we advise you to take out complete insurance with your own.
“Usually, young people are not yet able to properly apply their experience during an accident or even in driving,” says the director of the European insurance company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when drivers have already overcome the fears of beginners.
If the insured is already married but does not have children yet, it is best to take out complete insurance, of course, if its financial options allow it.
Insurance companies consider married couples with children as the lowest-risk customers, so in their case the fee payable is also lower.
In this case, it is best to have complete insurance with a self-sufficiency (which can reach 300 euros), or if they have a higher bonus, they can extend the insurance from the third year of the vehicle to the damage caused to others.
“They drive more calmly, but they have more customer power and they can afford to have a higher deductible,” confirms Luis Noguera.
In the case of pensioners, we recommend complete insurance with a self-sufficiency (which is around 150 euros) or, in the case of a higher bonus, it can be extended to liability insurance.
Car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it means protection for the owner in the event of damage events, but also because it means a large expense, so it is essential to choose the personalized form of insurance properly.
