At an exhibition of his works in Moderna Museet in 1968, with Warhol’s consent, hundreds of Brillo chests of cardboard were exhibited: These did not come from Warhol (for cost-savings) but were transported directly from the Brillo carton factory.
It was not about works of art, but about their templates, simple exhibition pieces.
However, Warhol gave permission in 1968 to manufacture some of the Brillo-trees in Sweden, which were not exhibited at Moderna Museet.
Witnesses of the time now speak of about fifteen boxes that, as authenticated at the time, as Original-Andy-Warhol-Brillo-Box, have rightly entered art and auction history under the designation "Stockholm type".
Some of them were auctioned off for more than 100,000 dollars.
The problem, however, is that Pontus Hultén, the legendary museum director later, falsely claimed that in 1968 a hundred wooden crates were produced and exhibited in Sweden, which were then left to him by Warhol.
In fact, 105 boxes of Hulén were produced in Malmö only in 1990 for an exhibition in St. Petersburg.
At that time, Warhol was dead for three years.
Lars Byström, the main monument manager of Moderna Museet, examined three privately owned boxes in Sweden, two of which were made in Stockholm in 1968: The pressed chipboards were first grounded and sanded, followed by a brush the white oil paint.
The structure of the copies from 1990, on the other hand, reveals that the paint was applied directly to the chipboard with a paint roller without foundation - and it is not oil, but acrylic paint.
"These boxes were not authenticated by the artist, so they should be deleted from the official list of Andy Warhol's Brillo Boxers," says Lars Nittve, director of Moderna Museet: "Unless the Andy Warhol Art Authentication Board of New York decides otherwise, Moderna Museet will classify the six crates in its collection as copies/exhibition material."
The Authentication Board announced in June that it would investigate “serious allegations” raised in connection with soap dust crates.
Since then, however, they have been wrapped in relentless silence.
